   {:e #blake3 "bc9e583d816d3feecc2740b1113f0f2ae9888c33b0299345f27288c7204889e9" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The attention pipeline (ATT-0..4) needs comprehensive testing. Each component introduces learnable state that could silently degrade if not verified. APPROACH: UNIT: (1) Surprisal = 1.0 for count=0, 0.5 for count=4, decreasing monotonically. (2) Hebbian boost increments on verbose request. (3) Hebbian decay halves per session (0.5^n). (4) Task relevance = 1.0 for matching namespace, 0.5 adjacent, 0.3 default. (5) Composite score combines all three factors correctly. (6) Block ordering follows composite score (highest first). PROPTEST: (7) For random presentation counts, surprisal is in (0, 1]. (8) For random attention scores, block ordering is total order (no ties cause instability). (9) Composite score is monotonically increasing in each factor when others held constant. E2E: (10) scripts/e2e_attention_pipeline.sh — multi-session scenario: init store, run 3 simulated sessions with varying verbose usage, verify block ordering evolves. Check: session 1 = default order, session 2 = verbose-boosted blocks higher, session 3 = task-switched blocks reorder. FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: Each assertion logs: block_label, surprisal, hebbian, task_rel, composite, expected_rank, actual_rank. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/tests/attention.rs + scripts/e2e_attention_pipeline.sh" :op :assert}
